	<ThingDef ParentName="AnimalThingBase" Name="Mashed_Spiribug_SpiribugThingBase" Abstract="True">
		<description>A small bird, often found with a belly coated in pollen. Highly adaptable, spiribugs are found almost everywhere, you just need to know where to look for them.\n\nNo one knows where spiribugs originally came from. Some cultures believe they are wandering souls, while others simply believe they are the result of some strange genetic experiment.\n\nSpiribugs have a unique relationship with the spiribush plant. They appear to be the only pollinator of the plant, and will often hide within spiribushes, only appearing when the bush is harvested for its flowers. Different species of spiribugs have affinities towards different coloured flowers, thus collecting specific types of pollen on their belly. This pollen can be collected off of their bellies, but only if the spiribug has become accustomed to human interaction.\n\nBoth wild and tame spiribugs are attracted to petalaces. They will occasionally visit anyone wearing a petalace, leaving some pollen on it in the process.</description>
		<descriptionHyperlinks>
			<ThingDef>Mashed_Spiribird_Spiribush</ThingDef>
		</descriptionHyperlinks>
		<modExtensions>
			<li Class="MorrowRim.ExtendedRaceProperties" MayRequire="SirMashedPotato.MorrowRim">
				<ashResistant>Resistant</ashResistant>
			</li>
		</modExtensions>
